### Parsing and Serializing HTTP Cookie Headers with Supabase SSR

Source: https://context7.com/supabase/ssr/llms.txt

Offers utilities for parsing HTTP cookie headers from incoming requests and serializing cookie data into a `Set-Cookie` header for outgoing responses. This is essential for managing session data and user preferences in SSR applications.

```typescript
import { parseCookieHeader, serializeCookieHeader } from '@supabase/ssr'

// Parse Cookie header from HTTP request
const cookieHeader = 'session=abc123; user_id=456; preferences=dark%20mode'
const parsed = parseCookieHeader(cookieHeader)
console.log(parsed)
// [
//   { name: 'session', value: 'abc123' },
//   { name: 'user_id', value: '456' },
//   { name: 'preferences', value: 'dark mode' }
// ]

// Serialize cookie for Set-Cookie header
const setCookieHeader = serializeCookieHeader('session', 'xyz789', {
  path: '/',
  httpOnly: true,
  secure: true,
  sameSite: 'strict',
  maxAge: 3600
})
console.log(setCookieHeader)
// 'session=xyz789; Path=/; HttpOnly; Secure; SameSite=Strict; Max-Age=3600'

// Using in a custom server framework
import { createServer } from 'http'
createServer((req, res) => {
  // Parse incoming cookies
  const cookies = req.headers.cookie
    ? parseCookieHeader(req.headers.cookie)
    : []

  const supabase = createServerClient(
    process.env.SUPABASE_URL!,
    process.env.SUPABASE_ANON_KEY!,
    {
      cookies: {
        getAll: () => cookies,
        setAll: (cookiesToSet) => {
          cookiesToSet.forEach(({ name, value, options }) => {
            const header = serializeCookieHeader(name, value, options)
            res.setHeader('Set-Cookie', header)
          })
        }
      }
    }
  )

  // Use supabase client...
}).listen(3000)
```

