### Utilize Supabase SSR Cookie Chunking for Large Data (TypeScript)

Source: https://context7.com/supabase/ssr/llms.txt

This snippet demonstrates how to use the `@supabase/ssr` utilities `createChunks`, `combineChunks`, `isChunkLike`, and `MAX_CHUNK_SIZE` to handle large data that exceeds typical cookie size limits. It shows how to split a large session string into multiple smaller cookie-compatible chunks, store them, and then reconstruct the original data from those chunks. The `isChunkLike` function helps identify if a cookie name belongs to a chunked series, and custom chunk sizes can be specified.

```typescript
import { createChunks, combineChunks, isChunkLike, MAX_CHUNK_SIZE } from '@supabase/ssr'

// Create chunks from a large value (e.g., session JSON)
const sessionData = JSON.stringify({
  access_token: 'very-long-jwt-token...',
  refresh_token: 'another-long-token...',
  user: { /* user object */ }
})

const chunks = createChunks('sb-access-token', sessionData)
// Returns: [
//   { name: 'sb-access-token.0', value: 'first 3180 chars...' },
//   { name: 'sb-access-token.1', value: 'next 3180 chars...' },
//   { name: 'sb-access-token.2', value: 'remaining chars...' }
// ]

// Store chunks as cookies
chunks.forEach(({ name, value }) => {
  document.cookie = `${name}=${encodeURIComponent(value)}; path=/; max-age=3600`
})

// Retrieve and combine chunks back into original value
const retrieveChunk = async (chunkName: string) => {
  const cookies = document.cookie.split('; ')
  const cookie = cookies.find(c => c.startsWith(`${chunkName}=`))
  if (!cookie) return null
  return decodeURIComponent(cookie.split('=')[1])
}

const reconstructed = await combineChunks('sb-access-token', retrieveChunk)
console.log(reconstructed === sessionData) // true

// Check if a cookie name is a chunk or chunk-like
console.log(isChunkLike('sb-access-token.0', 'sb-access-token')) // true
console.log(isChunkLike('sb-access-token', 'sb-access-token'))   // true
console.log(isChunkLike('sb-access-token.5', 'sb-access-token')) // true
console.log(isChunkLike('other-cookie', 'sb-access-token'))      // false

// Custom chunk size (default is 3180 bytes)
const smallChunks = createChunks('key', sessionData, 1000)
console.log(`Split into ${smallChunks.length} chunks`)
```
